msgstr "Canonical API name: `ptool.ssh.Connection:run`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:134
msgid "`conn:run(...)` executes a remote command through the current SSH connection."
msgstr "`conn:run(...)` ejecuta un comando remoto a través de la conexión SSH actual."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:136
msgid "The following call forms are supported:"
msgstr "Se admiten las siguientes formas de llamada:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:147
msgid "Argument rules:"
msgstr "Reglas de argumentos:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:149
msgid "`conn:run(cmdline)`: `cmdline` is sent as the remote command string."
msgstr "`conn:run(cmdline)`: `cmdline` se envía como la cadena de comando remoto."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:150
msgid "`conn:run(cmd, argsline)`: `cmd` is treated as the command, and `argsline` is split using shell-style (`shlex`) rules."
msgstr "`conn:run(cmd, argsline)`: `cmd` se trata como el comando, y `argsline` se divide usando reglas de estilo shell (`shlex`)."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:152
msgid "`conn:run(cmd, args)`: `cmd` is a string and `args` is an array of strings. Arguments are shell-quoted before remote execution."
msgstr "`conn:run(cmd, args)`: `cmd` es una cadena y `args` es un arreglo de cadenas. Los argumentos se escapan para shell antes de la ejecución remota."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:154
msgid "`conn:run(cmdline, options)`: `options` overrides this invocation."
msgstr "`conn:run(cmdline, options)`: `options` sobrescribe esta invocación."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:155
msgid "`conn:run(cmd, args, options)`: `options` overrides this invocation."
msgstr "`conn:run(cmd, args, options)`: `options` sobrescribe esta invocación."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:156
msgid "`conn:run(options)`: `options` is a table."
msgstr "`conn:run(options)`: `options` es una tabla."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:157
msgid "When the second argument is a table: if it is an array (consecutive integer keys `1..n`), it is treated as `args`; otherwise it is treated as `options`."
msgstr "Cuando el segundo argumento es una tabla: si es un arreglo (claves enteras consecutivas `1..n`), se trata como `args`; en caso contrario se trata como `options`."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:160
msgid "When `conn:run(options)` is used, `options` currently supports:"
msgstr "Cuando se usa `conn:run(options)`, `options` actualmente admite:"

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:162
msgid "`cmd` (string, required): The command name or executable path."
msgstr "`cmd` (string, obligatorio): Nombre del comando o ruta del ejecutable."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:163
msgid "`args` (string[], optional): The argument list."
msgstr "`args` (string[], opcional): Lista de argumentos."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:164
msgid "`cwd` (string, optional): Remote working directory. This is applied by prepending `cd ... &&` to the generated remote shell command."
msgstr "`cwd` (string, opcional): Directorio de trabajo remoto. Se aplica anteponiendo `cd ... &&` al comando shell remoto generado."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:166
msgid "`env` (table, optional): Remote environment variables, where keys and values are strings. This is applied by prepending `export ... &&` to the generated remote shell command."
msgstr "`env` (table, opcional): Variables de entorno remotas, donde claves y valores son cadenas. Se aplica anteponiendo `export ... &&` al comando shell remoto generado."

#: /Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:169
msgctxt "/Users/peterlits/Proj/PeterlitsZo/ptool/website/versioned_docs/version-0.5.0/lua-api/ssh.md:169"
msgid "`stdin` (string, optional): String sent to the remote process stdin."
msgstr "`stdin` (string, opcional): Cadena enviada al stdin del proceso remoto."

